<!-- ── SLIDE 08 · CP-SAT ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="slide" data-title="CP-SAT Strategy">
  <div class="badge badge-blue anim">Strategy 1</div>
  <h2 class="slide-title anim">CP-SAT — Mixed Integer Programming</h2>
  <p class="slide-sub anim">Exact solver using Google OR-Tools CP-SAT. Guarantees provable optimality within time budget.</p>

  <div class="grid-2 anim" style="max-width:960px">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Decision Variables</div>
      <ul class="fancy">
        <li><code style="color:var(--cyan)">x[app, QM]</code> — binary: is app assigned to this QM?</li>
        <li><code style="color:var(--cyan)">y[QM1, QM2]</code> — binary: is a channel needed between QMs?</li>
        <li><code style="color:var(--cyan)">z[prod, cons, QM1, QM2]</code> — binary: does flow route this path?</li>
        <li><code style="color:var(--cyan)">u[QM]</code> — binary: is this QM active (has ≥1 app)?</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Hard Constraints Enforced</div>
      <ul class="fancy">
        <li>Each app → <strong>exactly one</strong> QM (ExactlyOne)</li>
        <li>Each flow → <strong>exactly one</strong> route (ExactlyOne)</li>
        <li>Routing consistent with app placement (Implication)</li>
        <li>Cross-QM flows require channel existence (Implication)</li>
        <li>u[QM] = 1 iff any app assigned to it</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Weighted Minimization Objective</div>
      <div class="code">
minimize:
  α × total_channels          <span class="cm"># 1.0×</span>
+ β × cross_qm_hops           <span class="cm"># 2.0×</span>
+ γ × cross_lob_flows         <span class="cm"># 0.5×</span>
+ δ × new_objects_created     <span class="cm"># 1.0×</span>
+ ε × fanout_variance         <span class="cm"># 0.3×</span>
+ ζ × risky_app_moves         <span class="cm"># 5.0×</span>
      </div>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Scalability</div>
      <ul class="fancy">
        <li>Graph partitioning into connected components for datasets &gt;500 nodes</li>
        <li>Parallel solve of sub-components, then merge</li>
        <li>Time budget per solve: configurable (default 60s)</li>
        <li>Returns best incumbent if timeout reached</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── SLIDE 09 · CANONICAL HYBRID ──────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="slide" data-title="Canonical Hybrid">
  <div class="badge badge-cyan anim">Strategy 2</div>
  <h2 class="slide-title anim">Canonical Hybrid — Fast Heuristic</h2>
  <p class="slide-sub anim">Two-phase compression + greedy assignment. O(n log n) — suitable for real-time interactive feedback.</p>

  <div class="grid-2 anim" style="max-width:960px">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Phase 1 — Canonicalization</div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <span class="step-num">1</span>
        <span class="step-text"><strong>Logical Aggregation</strong> — collapses physical queue variants (`.RMT`, `.ALIAS`) into logical business queues</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <span class="step-num">2</span>
        <span class="step-text"><strong>Flow Group Formation</strong> — aggregates producer-consumer pairs by logical queue</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <span class="step-num">3</span>
        <span class="step-text"><strong>Weight Tracking</strong> — each flow group tracks source row count (message volume proxy)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Phase 2 — Greedy Assignment</div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <span class="step-num">1</span>
        <span class="step-text"><strong>Affinity Groups</strong> — connected-component clustering on producer-consumer graph</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <span class="step-num">2</span>
        <span class="step-text"><strong>Sort by Size</strong> — process largest groups first (greedy: solve hardest constraints early)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <span class="step-num">3</span>
        <span class="step-text"><strong>QM Selection</strong> — prefers QMs already hosting group members; minimizes load imbalance; uses seeded random tiebreaking</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <span class="step-num">4</span>
        <span class="step-text"><strong>Evaluate</strong> — formal lexicographic objective applied to final assignment</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="formula anim" style="margin-top:16px; max-width:860px">
    Logical Queue = strip_suffix(queue_name, ['.RMT', '.ALIAS', '.XA21', ...])
    <br>Affinity Group = connected_component(producer_consumer_graph)
  </div>
</section>

